# Manually-installed apt packages (output of `apt-mark showmanual`).
# Only packages that diverge from Ubuntu Server defaults are worth tracking —
# anything not here is "Ubuntu took care of it."
# Regenerate with: scripts/capture.sh
#
# ── varlock secrets plan (Stage 1, 2026-07-20) ────────────────────────────
# `pass` is the apt-side half of the varlock plan: GPG-encrypted tree
# underneath the committed `.env.schema` files in each project. It is
# installed but the store (and any GPG identity) are intentionally NOT yet
# initialized — that's Stage 2 (human TTY work). See AGENTS.md → "Varlock".
# `varlock` itself is a release-tarball binary, not apt; see
# packages/cargo.yaml → release_tarball_bins.

